FBIS4-64639 "drweu087_i_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 FRANCE Mitterand Sends Message To Nelson Mandela Mitterand Sends Message To Nelson Mandela LD0405215694 Paris Radio France International in French 2130 GMT 4 May 94 LD0405215694 Paris Radio France International French BFN [Text] In Paris, President Francois Mitterrand has sent a message to Nelson Mandela. The French president spoke about a magnificent success for all of South Africa because it is one of courage and dialogue. France, Mitterrand added, will [quote] deploy all its effort so a live, open, and fully responsible democracy blooms in South Africa, end of quote.
